    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hollandaise splits when the emulsion breaks, usually because the butter is melting too fast or the egg yolk is overheating. The heat is a bit too high, and the fat is separating from the protein. You can usually save it by cooling it down and whisking a little more yolk or a splash of lemon juice to re‑emulsify. If you’re unsure, just keep whisking until the sauce thickens again. It’s rarely truly ruined; it just needs a little more heat control.",
