    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To prevent splitting, you need to whisk the egg yolk and butter in a steady, rhythmic motion while keeping the pan at a gentle simmer. Add the butter in a slow, steady stream, and keep the mixture moving so the fat emulsifies completely. A small amount of warm water can help loosen the sauce, but it should be added gradually, a teaspoon at a time, while whisking. The key is to maintain a consistent temperature—too hot and it splits, too cold and it curdles. Next time, try whisking on a low heat until the sauce thickens, then turn off the heat and let it cool slightly before serving. This should give you a smooth, glossy hollandaise that holds together.",
